{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00222254632/1930082501/0588.xml":{"full_text":"20\n11 1 f r\nDrive Against Short Interests in Mart By Bulls Is Predicted\u2014Spectator\nPLAY ON UPSIDE IS SEEN\nFOR STOCK LEADERS\nThree-Day Holiday to4iold Up Operations\nt For Drive Until Next Week; Profit-\nTaking Advised for Week-End\nBy THE SPECTATOR\nThey\u2019re playing checkers still in the market with the bulls\nmaking most of the moves for the past week. Here and there\nthe bears nave been able to grab off a lone \u201cman\u201d or two by\nspecial drives against individual weak spots, but they haven\u2019t\nbeen able to get very far\nFirmness in the leaders has been able to keep the market\ntone strong and all weak stocks have come back aggressively\nafter every reaction This strengthens the general feeling that\n-t hi B \u00abt a play on the upside after the stormy time\nit has befen through for almost a year.\nThis week, however, will end in a three-day holiday. This\nwid probably hold operations for the rise in check. At that I\n-look for strength today and probably tomorrow, directed mainly\nagainst the short interests. If it develops I advise week-end\nprofit taking for I believe the market will sag off by the end\nof the week Those who haven\u2019t entered the market yet should\nwait. There is still time to get aboard the bandwagon.\nThe Torchbearer\n'jj. S. Steel has been acting\nwell all week. It is apparently\nbeing well bought. Further\nstrength today would indicate\nanother cheerful Iron Age re\nport on Wednesday. Even if it\nfails to develop this week, the\nadverse effect will be only tem\nporary.\nThere will be some seasonal\nimprovement in the steel indus\ntry and this cannot be long de\nlayed. Increase in scrap steel\nprices in both Pittsburgh and\nChicago last week is encouraging.\nThe whole financial community\nthe market action of\nsteel very closely. Its Jiigh since\nthe June break was 170%, but\nit failed to show any volume\nthrough 170, a sign that the\npowers that be were opposed to\nany advance and were supplying\nstock freely. This meant a re\naction, which came.\nWhen steel crosses 170% and\ngoes up on big volume, it will\nbe the signal for a real move in\nthe whole market.\nInterests close to Goodyear\nTire are now looking ahead to\nriext year. They don\u2019t expect\nany favorable developments fov\nthe rest of this year. Earnings\nare down sharply from 1929, and\noperations were recently reduced\nagain. The crude rubber situa\ntion has been bad. I understand\nthere hasn\u2019t been any effort to\nsupport Goodyear market-wise\nand it may go lower. Insiders,\nhowever, are bullish over the\nlong term outlook see res\ntoration of real earnings when\nbusiness recovers.\nA Happy Family\nThese seem to be the days\nwhen the bulls and bears are\ntaking big swigs out of the old\noaken bucket together and call\ning each other by their first\nnames.. The last operation In\nBriggs was credited to Ben Smith,\nand he is said to be working in\nthe stock again. John Pope is\nreported to have taken a big\nlong position in Radio Keith\nOrpheum. Now I hear Danforth,\nthe so-called \u201cBoston bear,\u201d re\ncently bought a wad of Ford, Ltd.\nAll that is needed is for Liver\nmore to buy a share or two of\nsomething, and the family picture\nwould be complete.\na The growing national desire to\nhave a real American merchant\nmarine helps the long-tetrm out\nlook for the shipping shares.\nEarnings, however, have been\nvery unstable, and the lower\nvolume of world trade this year,\nas forecast, makes the outlooK\nfor the rest of the year bad.\nCompanies most favorably situ\nated are American Ship Building.\nCO-DPERATIVE\n15 FORMED\n*\u201cA co-operative marketing ar\nrangement has been agreed upon\nfay the Cha\u2019leng\u00ae Cream and But\nter Association, the United Dairy\nmen\u2019s Association and the Inter\nstate Associated Creameries, the\nFederal Farm Board was advised\ntoday. The headquarters of the\nco-operative movement will be in\nPbrtland, Ore.\nThe three organizations repre\nsent 33,000 producers with an\nnual sales exceeding 135,000 000.\n'William F. Schilling, dairy\nmember of the Farm Board, said:\n\u201cWith the completion of this\nmarketing arrangement between\nthese large co-operative produc\nIng organizations practically\nall of the best quality butter\nmanufactured in the West Coast\n-States is brought under cen\n'tralized co-ooerative control.\nScott Paper Sales Up\n$328,001 in 7 Months\nScott Paper Co. reported today\nnet sales for the seven months\nended July were M.M2.C23\nAginst M. 434.631 in the like 1929\nWASHINGTON TIHESt FINANCIAL NEWS\nAtlantic Gulf and West Indies,\nEastern Steamship, and U. S.\nLines.\nRough Going\nThe boot and shoe industry is\nentering the close of an unsatis\nfactory year. Production volume\nhas been down from 1929 and\nthe hand-to-mouth buying by the\npublic has affected sales. Inven\ntories are said to be large. High\ner tariff duties helped the feeling\nin the industry. The leaders are\nin a strong position and, while\nable to make money even in a\ndepression year, there seems little\nimmediate chance for a while of\nany sustained upward movement\nin their shares. There are, how\never, longterm possibilities for\nthose desiring semi-in vestments.\nThe best stocks in this grbup are\nBrown Shoe, Florsheim. Interna\ntional Shoe, Melville and I. Mil\nler.\nThompson Starrett, mentioned\nhere some time ago as a good\nlow-priced bet if the outlook for\nthe building industry improved,\ncame to life Saturday with a two\npoint advance. Earnings for the\nfirst quarter were only slightly be\nlow the same period in 1929, and\nthe company has a good volume\nof business on its books. The\naction of the stock indicates a\nquick play but I wouldn't-advise\nfollowing the move too far.\nHere and There\nAmerican Machine and Foun\ndry, recommended here a few\ndays ago, came through with an\nadvance of almost 3 points to a\nnew high for the year. It looks\nlike a good trading bet, and has\nreal long-term appeal. I shouldn\u2019t\nbe surprised to see a drive against\nthe bears in Burroughs Adding\nMachine. I understand it has a\nlarge sleeping short interest.\nSam Smith says the bears are\nlooking for a party and they are\ngoing to get a squeeze.\nAmerican International should\nwake up one of these days with\na good-sized advance. Higher\nstock prices enhance the value\nof its portfolio and its own\nworth.\nDupont looks like one of the\nbest bets on the list on any weak\nness. There is a strong group\nworking in General Motors, and\nI expect a good move in motors.\nDu Pont will go up two points\nto motors one.\nThere is a lot of bullishness\naround on American and Foreign\nPower and they\u2019re talking of a\nbig move. Activity in Philadel\nphia and Reading Coal and Iron\nlooks like formation of a new\npool on improved operations in\nthe coal industry. Well-informed\npeople are bullish on Chrysler\u2019s\nlong-pull prospectw\nADVANCE PRICE\nOF PENN OIL\nPITTSBURGH, Aug. 22 (1.N.5.).\nRegarded as the most heartening\nsign of recovery in oil production\noperations in recent months, an\nadvance of 25 cents per barrel in\nthe price of Pennsylvania grade,\ncrude oil, was announced here\ntoday by the Seep Purchasing\nCompany of the South Penn Oil\nCompany.\nThe advance today brings the\nprice of Pennsylvania grade up to\n$2.30 per barrel.\nCo-incidential with the boost in\nPennsylvania grade was the an\nnouncemen by the Tidewater Oil\nCompany of an advance of 35\ncents per barrel in Bradford grade,\nbringing the price of Bradford up\nto $2.50 per barrel.\nPennsylvania grade. Southwest\nPipe Line, advanced 25 cents per\nbarrel to 2J5. and Pennsylvania\ngrade. Eureka Pipe Line, was\nstepped up to $2.15 per barrel.\nToday\u2019s advances marked the\nfirst price boost since January 4.\n1929.\nA rar far vaa aarf aae far tbr\nUy raa bafta br par.-haard far 'be\nprtae at a \u2014ara raa tbraagh taAay's\ni rtwMM Aa.\nTHfc WASHINGTON TIMES\nOptimist\ni\n\nHLr\nv a\nI\nIk HL\n\u2014Time* Staff Photo\nALFRED P. SLOAN. JR.\nPRESIDENT OF General Mo\ntors Corporation, who sees a\ngood future for the automobile\nindustry. Mr. Sloan believes\nthat there are a great number\nof automobile orders that have\nbeen held up by the recent de\npression that will soon be ac\nquired. This he says, in addi\ntion to the regular orders, will\nswell the total to boom propor\ntions.\nbrokers SEE\nFUTURE RISE\nA continuation of the upward\nmovement was forecast in broker- j\nage circles today.\nThe technical position appears j\nto us particularly sound. Stocks\nare and have been working into\nstrong hands. The least little bit\nof encouraging trade news should\nhasten the upturn which we be\nlieve is in the making.\u2014BAA\u00df,\nCOHEN CO.\nThe immediate technical indi\ncations show no change as com\npared with the past few days.\nSelling in the important active\nleaders fails to make any headway\ndespite isolated weakness in a few\nindividual issues. For the past\nthree days reactions have halted\naround the same point each day.\nIt has all the appearance of in\nterests committed to higher prices.\n\u2014OTIS CO.\nCareful purchases on weak\nspots in the best trading profits\nwithin a few weeks.\u2014E. F. HUT\nTON CO.\nLook for further strength in\nactive leading issues for the near\nfuture and would continue to buy\nsound stocks on all moderate re\ncessions in prices.\u2014TOBEY <fc\nKIRK.\nContinue to have faith in the\nmarket. Hold stocks over the\nweek-en d\u2014HORNBLOWER\nWEEKS.\nThe tape still shows quiet\nstrength and the trend looks up\nward.\u2014M. J. MEEHAN CO.\nThe stock market appears to\nhave touched bottom, temporarily\nat least. We are of the opinion\nthe lows have been seen, although\na broad upturn at this time would\n\u201cbe premature.\u2014PASK WAL\nBRIDGE.\nFeel that circumstances will\ncontinue favorable into next\nmonth at least, or until it can be\ndefinitely ascertained whether the\nbusiness revival is still to be\nfurther delayed. JOHN MUIR\nCO.\nRecent strength in stock prices\nis continued evidence of profes\nsional tactics rather than the\nentrance into the market of real\ninvestment buying in large vol\nume.\u2014J. S. BACHE CO.\nFALL RIVER GAS WORKS\nBOSTON, Aug. 25.\u2014The Fall\nRiver Gas Works has petitioned\nthe Massachusetts Department of\nPublic Utilities for authority to\nissue 13,236 additional shares of\nstock of $25 to be issued at $37.50\na share. Funds are to be used to\nretire funded debt.\nA Good\nReconditioned\nCar\nwill add much\nto your Labor\nDay week end:\nselect the one\nbest suited to\nyour transporta\ntion needs from\ntoday\u2019s\u2014\nTimes Classified Ads\nOptimism Gains Hold\nAs Summer Season\nEnters Final Week\nOptimism is gaining a fiyne\nfoothold, as the summer vacation\nseason enters its final week.\nFavorable news is outweighing\nthe unfavorable. People are pay\ning more attention to the present,\nand their jobs, as the realization\nis brought home that two and\ntwo make four and not five or\nsix.\nThe drought, which has had a\ndepressing effect on sentiment\nand extended the cautious buying\nperiod is behind us. There has\nbeen some improvement in busi\nness, and further evidence of this\nis found in the trade reports and\nnews of this week. Everything\npoints to a continuance of this\ntrend at least through the\nautumn months, with the possi\nbility of some slowing down dur\ning the winter and a sustained\nrecovery in the spring.\nThe stock market has extended\nits gains in the face of stiff op\nposition. If it is able to resist\nany substantial liquidation of se\ncurities in the next two months\nit is safe to assume the lows of\nlast June will not be seen for\nsome time.\nMarket at August 1 Levels\nThe stock market has swung\nback to around July\u2019s closing lev\nels. Practically all groups, with\nthe exception of the rails, have\nmade up the losses sustained the\nfirst of this month. The rebound\nhas been as sharp as the decline\nand is due entirely to profes\nsional operators.\nThe market started up Friday\na week ago, turned reactionary\nSaturday. The selling was con\ntinued with the resumption of\ntrading Monday, but in the after\nnoon the decline was checked and\nstocks mov d forward. This move\nwas carried through to Thursday\nmorning, when there was a mod\nerate setback, but yesterday the\ngeneral trend was upward.\nTrading has been light,\nfurther evidence of the profes\nsional character of the market.\nThe rails were sold chiefly be\ncause of the uncertainty of the\ndrought\u2019s effect on freight traffic\nand little hope for any sharp up\nturn in carrier earnings this year.\nThe coppers were under pressure\nall week, with Anaconda and\nKennecott establishing new lows.\nSales of metal at 10% cents a\npound and fears of further divi\ndend cuts brought on the selling.\nThe motors were quiet, with Gen\neral Motors gaining slightly on\nthe week. Some of the good\ngainers were Johns Manville.\nWoolworth, Otis Elevator and big\nSteel.\nLOCAL STOCKS\nCapital Traction Company, 10\n61; 10@60%.\nWash Railway and. Electric, pre\nferred, 10@98 1 /2.\nColumbia Sand <fc Gravel, pre\nferred, 3 @94.\nAfter Call\nPotomac Electric, s\u2019/is preferred,\n15@109; 5@109.\nPotomac Electric Cons ss, SI,OOO\n@lO3.\nMerchants Bank and Trust, 10\n@125.\nCapital Traction Company, 10\n60%; 10@61; 10@61%.\nPoblle Utility Bon<1\u00bb I Kid i Aak\nAmer T T 414\u00ab \u201933 1101\nAmer Tel Tel 414 s \u201939....|161\nAin Tel Tel CtT Tr 55..|105\nAnacostla Pot R R 5a..1 82141\nAna Pot Guar os 92141\nCAP Tel of Va 5s 102' I\nCap Traction R R 5s 93 j 94\nCity Suburban 5s 80 1 52\nGeorgetown Gai Ist 6s 103\nPotomac Elec Cons 5s 110214 103\nPotomac Elec 5s '53 |IOB\nWash Alex Mt V ctf. .1 6\nWash Balto An 5s I 50 I so\nWashington Gas 6s 1103 110414\nWash Gas 6s Series A [lO3 1103%\nWash Gas 6s series B 1105\nWash Ry Elec 4s Bi>%\u2018 90\nMiscellaneous Bonds I\nBarber Ross Inc 6145....1 89 I 90\nChevy Chase Club 5*45..... .1100 I\nD. C. Paper Mfg'6s 50 75\nW. M. Cold Storage 5s I 95 1\nWash Cons 'Title 6s 89 1100\nPublic Utility Stocks I\nAtner Tel Tel 1212 L....\nCapitol Traction Co 60%1*61 U\nWash Gas Lt Co 1121 11.30\nN W Steamboat |\u20194O [255\n\u2022Pot Elec Pow 6s pfd [no \u2019ll2\n\u2666Pot Elec Pw 514 s pfd.... 108\u2019i 10914\n\u2022Wash Ry El c0m...... |SOO 1...\nWash Ry A El pf<i 98\u20194 j 99\nNatjonal liank stocks I\nCapital 2?,~\nColumbus 1400 [440\nCommercial (stamped) 1225 240\nDi\u00abtrlct |212 f 250\nW. B. HIBBS CO.\nThe ONLY New York Stock Exchange House\nHaving Its Main Office in Washington\nMEMBERS\nNew York Stock Exchange\nBoston Stock Exchange\nPhiladelphia Stock Exchange\nWashington Stock Exchange\nNew York Cotton Exchange\nChicago Board of Trade\nAmerican Bankers Association\nDistrict Bankers Association\n151\n\nHIBBS BUILDING\nNational 0540 WASHINGTON, D. C.\nTha National Daily\nThe listed bond market is con\ntinuing its encouraging steady ad\nvance to new high prices for the\nyear. This, with an expansion for\nthe second consecutive week in\ncommercial loans by banks, fur\nnishes the most comfort in the\npresent situation.\nBond financing, however, last\nweek was the second lightest\nfor the year. A total of $28,539,-\n500 in new issues were put upon\nthe market. This compares with\nthe week before\u2019s total of $30,-\n767,000 and $54,515,000 in the cor\nresponding week a year ago. Last\nweek\u2019s loans were practically all\nfor municipal governments. There\nwas one foreign issue\u2014-a $2,680,000\nloan for Bergen. Norway.\nThe month\u2019s total, however, is\nnot far behind the amount placed\na year ago. To date this month\n$435,000,000 bond issues have been\nbrought out, against $145,000,000\nin August, 1929. There are several\nlarge offerings being prepared, in\ncluding a $50,000,000 public utility\nloan.\nHighlights of News\nThe suit for receivership against\nWarner Bros. Pictures, Inc., was\nthe week\u2019s outstanding .news de\nvelopment, and followed a pool\nmanipulation in the stock earlier\nin the year, a sharp drop in earn\nnigs in the final half of the year,\nand the passing of the dividend\ntwo weeks ago. Suit charges mis\nmanagement.\nThe high cost of competition in\nthe oil industry was emphasized\nwith the passing of dividends by\nWarner Quinlan Co. and Shell\nUnion Oil Co. The latter is the\npowerful British controlled Royal\nDutch Shell American subsidiary,\nwhile the former is one of the\nleading independent gasoline dis\ntributors in Metropolitan New\nYork. <Both have been combating\nthe Standard Oil Companies.\nHudson Motor Car Co. cut its\ndividend rate from $5 to $3.\nPan-American Airways com\npleted arrangements for a merger\nwith New York-Rio-Bunos Aires\nAir Line, giving the United States\nfirst rank in air lines in South\nAmerica.\nFox Film earnings increased 40\nper cent.\nLOADINGS DECLINE\nCHICAGO, Aug. 25.\u2014Loadings\nof revenue freight on the Chicago.\nMilwaukee, St. Paul Pacific in\nthe first 21 days of the current\nmonth totaled 114,136 cars against\n138,615 revenue freight cars han\ndled in the corresponding period\nof last year.\nBid Ask\nFederai-American i 275 1300\nLiberty [2OO 1320\nLincoln 1400 440\nMetropolitan ....|350 |4OO\nRigg 526\nSecond |176 1214\nWashington [246 1255\nTrust (ompany Stocks I I\nAmer Sec Tr Co. (385 ,40b\nContinental Trust 1120 1140\nMerck Bk Tr .....125 [l5O\nNafl Sav Tr [545 1600\nUnion Trust ,255 1300\nWash Loan A Tr 1465 510\nSavings Bank Stocks I I\nBank of Bethesda 59 65\nCommerce Savings 330\nEast Washington 25 35\nPotomac Savings Bank 65 75\nSec Sav A Coral Bk 471 500\nSeventh Street 1315 I\nUnited States [530 \u2018630\nWash Mechanics 50\nFire Insnrance Stocks I\nAmerican [320\nCorcoran [l5O I\nFiremen\u2019s I 32 I 38\nNational Union I 22 f 26\nTitle Insurance Stocks i I\nColumbia 8 A4' 12\nReal Estate 155 175\nTitle A Ihv Co Md com.. ..I 20 I 30\n.Miscellaneous Stocks I I\nBarber A Rosa Inc com. I 15 I 16\n\u2022Chevy Chase Dairy pfd.... 102 \u2018lO9\nCol Sand A Grav pfd I 90 94\nCol Medical Bldg C0rp....\u2018100\nD C Paper Mfg pfd I 70 I\nDistrict National Sec pfd,..' 70 I 85\nEmer Bromo-Seix \"A\u201d.., ..I 30 33\nFederal Storage pfd >llO >125\nFed-Amer Co comm I 31 i 33\nFsd-Amer Co pfd '99 100\n\u2022Lanston Monotype 1114 [ll\u00dfl4\nMer Tr A Stge com [lO3 1110\nMar Tr A Stge pfd 9514 TOO\nMergenthaler Lino 96 i 9714\nNatl Mtge A Inv pfd 5 I 5>4\nPeoples Drug S pfd 10214 105\nReal Eat. M A G pfd 614'\nSecurity Storage 112 114\nTer Ref A Wh C0rp....... 47 52\nThe Carpel Corp 23 24\nW Meeh Mlge com 814\nWash Med Bldg Corp 1\u00bb5\nWoodward A Lothrop pfd. .107 1112\n\u2666Ed. dividends.\nMONDAY, AVGUST RB, 1030\nNANIPULATION\nBYPOOLSHURT\nMANY STOCKS\nPetitions For Receiverships\nPoint to Mismanagement\nBy Company Officials\nBy EDWABD DIXON\nDuring the past nine months\nmore than a half-dozen petitions\nhave been identified with pool\nfor receivers have been filed\nagainst companies whose stocks\noperations on the New York\nStock Exchange and New York\nCurb Exchange.\nIn a majority of instances the\nreceivership petitions claimed\nmismanagement by officials of\nthe various companies involved.\nThe latest petition, that against\nWarner Brothers Pictures, Inc.,\nfollows closely on top of the pass\ning of the dividend on the com\nmon stock.\nPeculiarly enough, in almost\nevery case, the developments\nwhich eventually resulted in the\npetition for receiver were the\nsame.\nInvestigations Ordered\nExpansion programmes were\nprogressing rapidly. Large sums\nof money were being spent for ad\nditions to plants, purchasing new\nsites, etc. During the course of\nthe expansion programme the\nstocks of such companies were\nsubjected to sharp upswings and\nwere usually very actively dealt\nin. The first indication that pro\ngress was not as satisfactory as\nhad been expected usually came\nin the way of a let-down in earn\nings. Then followed the passing\nof the dividend.\nIn several cases the violent fluc\ntuations of the stock of these\ncompanies have brought about\ninvestigations by Stock Exchange\nauthorities and even the State\nAttorney-General.\nManhattan Electrical Supply is\nprobably the outstanding example\nof pool operation in this respect.\nThe investigation which followed\nthe precipitate break in the price\nof the stock revealed that cus\ntomers\u2019 men had been bribed\nwith cash and \u201ccalls\u201d to recom\nmend the purchase of the stock\nto their customers. At the time\nof the filing of the petition for\nJgL BACK HOME\n|B, t YCURSIOHR\nMidwestern points\nmLM(o sy n) TICKETS ON SALE\nSflWllllfr? 2Z AUGUST 29th\nAT ONE-HALF PRICE\nFirst Time Such Radical Reductions Made in\nRailroad Tickets Good for 30 Days Exceptional\nOpportunity for Vacation or Visit Back Home\nEXCURSION FARES\nFROM WASHINGTON RADICAL FARE REDUCTIONS\nTo Pitt.lmr f l> P. SIO.M Ti\u20acl u wil| u m\n10 Wheeling, W. Va.. 14.73 round trip to Pittsburgh, Wheeling, Parkersburg\nTo Parkersburg, W.Va. 12.86 \u201cJ e T\u00b0. f inc, din Ci\u00ab\u00abn-\n\"p U w ir \u00a3o nati, Louisville, Detroit, Indianapolis, St. Lotus\n10 Huntington, W.Va. 15.b0 and Chicago. (See specific fares in column.)\nTo New Castle, Pa... 12.69 proportionately low fares from\nTo Youngstown, 0... 13.24 annapolis and Baltimore.\nTo Akron, 015.16\n\u2122ta U o.\u2019. 18.65 TICKETS GOOD FOR 30 DAYS--\nTo Toledo, 0 19.48 Tickets will be sold Aug. 29th only, good for\nTo Detroit, Mich.... 21.55 return until Sept. 27th. Stop-overs permitted.\nTo Gary, 1nd26.59\nTo Chicago, H[\u00ab TICKETS GOOD ON ALL TRAINS\u2014\nTo Zanesville, 0 15.72\nTo Newark, 0 16.59 Tickets will be honored in coaches or sleeping\n*r n i L n i, TO ear (p* u regular Pullman charge) on ALL\n10 Lolumbus, U 17.73 TRAINS, going trip to begin Aug. 29th.\nTo Chillicothe, 0.../: 16.62\nTo Dayton, 0 19.50\nTo Cincinnati, 0 20.15\nTo Indianapolis, Ind.. 24.10 TRAVEL BUREAU and CITY TICKET OFFICE\nTo Vincennes, Ind.. Woodward Bldg., 15th and H Sts. N. W.\nTo Louisville, Ky.... 23.72\nTo Springfield, 1115... 31.20\nT C* r M \u00abC 4 PHONE: DISTRICT SSM\n10 it. LOUIS, Mo 34.54 D u MOORMAN Assistant General Passenger Agent\nProportionately Lew Fares te\nOther Points\nBALTIMORE OHIO\nWall Street\nHears\nThat a large new pool has\nbeen formed in Radio (R).\nThat Canadian interests have\nbeen buying International\nNickel (N), which is expected\nto do better when the rights\nare oat of the Way.\nThat a good-sized short in\nterest exists in American Can\n(AC).\nThat traders are switching\nout of Kennecott (KN) be\ncause of the uncertainty over\nthe dividend action.\nThat Chemical National As\nsociates, on the Curb, should go\nup when it is merged with the\nChemical Bank.\nThat Union Carbide (UN) is\nbeing accumulated.\nThat unless the earnings of\nSims Petroleum (SV) improve,\nthe dividend will be cut.\na receiver, it was claimed that\nmore than $6,000,000 had been\nlost by the public through the\npool\u2019s operations.\nThe Bolster Crash\nBolster Radio Corporation was\nanother stock that was exploited\nby pool manipulation. During the\ninvestigation conducted by the\nVice Chancellor of New Jersey it\nwas brought out that Ellery W.\nStone, president of the company\nand alter one of the receivers ap\npointed by the court, had made a\nprofit of $698,000 through trading\nin the stock. Stone claimed, how\never, that he had never partici\npated in any pool operations in\nthe stock, having bought and sold\nhis holdings in the open market.\nRudolf Spreckels, chairman of the\nboard of Bolster, testified that\nduring the years 1927, 1928 and\n1929 he had made a profit of ap\nproximately $13,000,000 in selling\nBolster's stock.\nThe public took another \u201click\ning\u201d in Celotwt, which vied with\nManhattan Electrical Supply for\nthe rapidity of its rise and fall.\nBror Dahlberg, head of the com\npany, issued denials, at the time\napplication was made for receiver\nship, of reports that his company\nwas not in a sound, prosperous\ncondition. The application for re\nceiver eventually was dismissed\nby the Delaware court.\nCUBES fO E-ND\nDEPRESSION\nIS URGED\nNoted Economists Study\nMeans to End Slumps Simi\nlar to That Just Ended\nBy LEWIS HANEY,\nDirector New York University Bureau\nof Business Research and\nEconomist of Federal Trade\nCommission\nWe are all now looking for\nward to the time when business\nrecovery will set in. We are also\nseeking means to relieve the hard\nships of those suffering from de\npressed conditions, and to hasten\nthe recovery time. Naturally a\ngood many proposed remedies are\nup for discussion.\nFor example, a well-known\nCleveland bank of.'i \u2018al tells us\nthat holidays 'and winter shut\ndowns in the circus business are\nlike business depressions. He\nargues that in uch cases we\nmerely make preparations in ad\nvance and suffer little disturb\nance as a result. The implication\nis that we shou 1 see business de\npressions coming and accumulate\nreserves to tide us .\u2019er. Then we\nmight \u201cslide down comfortably\nand sa-'ely.\u201d\nMust Prevent Depressions\nBut such a procedure would\ntake the depressions for granted.\nWhat we want is to prevent de\npressions, for it is inevitable that\nmany will be unable to make ade\nquate provision for them. Surely\nit is not very comforting to say\nthat we must go ahead and com\nmit the same business excesses of\nover-production and speculative\ninflation,' merely trying to save up\nenough to tide us over the in\nevitable recession.\nBusiness depressions are de\ncidedly different from regular\nholidays and periods of seasonal\nlet down. The latter are regular,\nand we know just when they come\nand how long they will last. Above\nall they are not due to overpro\nouction and inflation.\nOthers are seeking remedies\nthrough government aid. They\nwant new loan corporations and\nmore credit. They urge the gov\nernment to anticipate its pur\nchases of materials and its con\nstruction of roads, etc.","height":"30445","width":"24194"}}
